    {
      "page_number": 1,
      "raw_text": "The projected Spokane & Kootenai\nbranch of the Canadian Pacific rail-\nroad line for which surveying parties\nhave been at work since the early\npart of the year have SO far pro-\ncrossed with their work that they\nnow have but little more than 80\nmiles yet to map.\n\n\nThe line will leave Yahk in British\nColumbia on the C. p. r. line, where\nthe connection with that line will be,\nand will follow the course OF the\nMoyie river down to the junction of\nthat river with the Kootenay river at\na point about three miles east Of\nBonners Ferry. Crossing the river\nthere. the route will be on the south\nside Of the Kootenay and on the OPP\nposite side Of the river from the\nGreat Northern track."
    }
  ]
